verbose_text: Control inhibitors stabilize naive and primed pluripotent states as expected; LIF-Jak-Stat3 inhibition by ruxolitinib and tofacitinib promotes a primed signature (low Nanog, high Dnmt3b; XREF_FIG B), while the Fgfr inhibitors PD173074 and AZD4547 or the Mek1/2 inhibitors PD0325901 and PD184352 promote a naive signature (high Nanog, low Dnmt3b; XREF_FIG B).
